==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Amphipoda
<hw>Am*phip"o*da</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>'amfi`</grk> + <?/, <?/ foot.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A numerous group of fourteen -- footed Crustacea, inhabiting both
fresh and salt water. The body is usually compressed laterally, and the
anterior pairs or legs are directed downward and forward, but the
posterior legs are usually turned upward and backward. The beach flea is
an example. See <er>Tetradecapoda</er> and
<er>Arthrostraca</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amphipodous</ent>⟦br⟧
